---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="How Much is 1TB? What Can You Store?" description="Understand how much data fits in 1 terabyte of storage. Real-world examples of photos, videos, songs, and documents you can store on a 1TB drive." keywords="1TB storage, terabyte explained, how much is 1TB, storage capacity, 1TB photos, 1TB movies, hard drive capacity">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Data</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">How Much is 1TB? What Can You Store?</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 3, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>You are shopping for a hard drive or choosing a cloud storage plan and the options are 256 GB, 512 GB, 1 TB, or 2 TB. But what does a terabyte actually hold? Here are real-world numbers to help you decide.</p>

      <h2>What is a Terabyte?</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">1 TB = 1,000 GB = 1,000,000 MB</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Note: Your computer may show ~931 GB due to binary vs decimal counting</p>
      </div>

      <h2>What 1 TB Can Hold</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Photos (smartphone, 5 MB each):</strong> approximately 200,000 photos</li>
        <li><strong>Photos (DSLR RAW, 40 MB each):</strong> approximately 25,000 photos</li>
        <li><strong>Songs (MP3, 5 MB each):</strong> approximately 200,000 songs (1,370 days of music)</li>
        <li><strong>Movies (HD, 4 GB each):</strong> approximately 250 movies</li>
        <li><strong>Movies (4K, 10 GB each):</strong> approximately 100 movies</li>
        <li><strong>Documents (Word, 50 KB each):</strong> approximately 20 million documents</li>
        <li><strong>eBooks (5 MB each):</strong> approximately 200,000 books</li>
        <li><strong>Video games (50 GB each):</strong> approximately 20 games</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Choosing the Right Storage Size</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>128-256 GB:</strong> Good for casual users — documents, some photos, a few apps</li>
        <li><strong>512 GB:</strong> Enough for most people — moderate photo library, some games, all your apps</li>
        <li><strong>1 TB:</strong> Great for photographers, gamers, or anyone with a large media collection</li>
        <li><strong>2-4 TB:</strong> For video editors, extensive game libraries, or family media servers</li>
        <li><strong>8+ TB:</strong> Professional video production, large data archives, NAS systems</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How Fast Does 1 TB Fill Up?</h2>
      <p>Depending on your usage:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Light user</strong> (office work, browsing): Years to fill</li>
        <li><strong>Photographer</strong> (100 RAW photos/week): About 5 years</li>
        <li><strong>Gamer</strong> (2-3 new games/month): 6-12 months</li>
        <li><strong>Video creator</strong> (4K footage): 1-3 months</li>
        <li><strong>Streaming downloads</strong> (Netflix offline): Depends on quality, HD fills ~250 movies</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>TB in the Cloud</h2>
      <p>Cloud storage pricing for 1 TB (approximate monthly costs):</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google One: 1 TB included with some Google Workspace plans</li>
        <li>iCloud+: Included with Apple One Premier</li>
        <li>OneDrive: 1 TB included with Microsoft 365 Personal</li>
        <li>Dropbox Plus: 2 TB for individual plan</li>
      </ul>
      <p>For most individuals, 1 TB of cloud or local storage is more than sufficient for years of everyday use.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/data" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Data Converter →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/convert/data" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Converter →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
